content: 'We encourage submissions of high quality papers on all topics in the general areas of databases, information retrieval, and knowledge management. Papers should contain previously unpublished work and not be under submission to other conferences or journals.
Label: N

content: 'Details on how to submit to CIKM 2011 are available on the submissions page.
Label: N

content: 'Papers that bridge across these areas are of special interest and will be considered for a "Best Interdisciplinary Paper" award. Topics of interest in the three areas include, but are not limited to:
Label: N

content: 'Database languages and models (e.g., fuzzy data, probabilistic databases, meta-data management)
Label: I

content: 'Dynamic aspects of databases (updates, views, real-time data, sensor data, active databases, data streams)
Label: I

content: 'Mobile, parallel and distributed data management (including cloud computing)
Label: I

content: 'Semi-structured data processing, XML filtering and routing
Label: I

content: 'Workflow, Web services and Web Service Composition
Label: I

content: 'Cross-language retrieval, Multilingual retrieval, Machine translation for IR
Label: I

content: 'Evaluation, Test collections, Crowdsourcing for IR evaluation
Label: I

content: 'HCIR, User Interfaces, Interactive IR, User models, User studies
Label: I

content: 'Language technologies for IR (NLP, IE, Summarization, QA, ...)
Label: I

content: 'Multimedia IR: audio, speech, image, video, and cross-media
Label: I

content: 'Other topics related to IR (Adverserial IR, Advertising, Privacy, Text Mining, etc.)
Label: I

content: 'Knowledge and privacy (e.g., privacy-preserving data publishing and mining)
Label: I

content: 'Mining the usage, consumption and production of resources
Label: I

content: 'Industry authors are invited to submit papers describing solutions in the domains addressed by this conference, focusing on the technical aspects of their work. The submission procedure for industrial papers is the same as for research papers.
Label: N

content: 'ACM CIKM review is double-blind. Therefore, please anonymise your submission. Non-anonymous submissions will be rejected. If your CIKM 2011 submission is an extension of a previously-published workshop paper the contributions beyond that workshop paper should be discussed in the related work section, referencing the workshop paper as an anonymous citation.
Label: N

content: 'All accepted papers will be published in the ACM CIKM proceedings, which will be distributed in CD format at the conference. All papers will be indexed in the ACM digital library.
Label: N

content: 'Conference co-Chairs: Iadh Ounis (University of Glasgow) and Ian Ruthven (University of Strathclyde)
Label: I

Label: I
